body: The EAP for `2021.1` is now available; we should update the plugin to support it.

comment_data.body:
In the meantime, the latest 52.2.5 seems to work okay for now by manually changing the maximum version from `203.*` to `211.*` in the `plugin.xml` file.

[flutter-intellij.zip](https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/files/5890792/flutter-intellij.zip)

I've observed a crash when launching the IDE with the modified plugin loaded. I'm mentioning it here in case it's useful to achieving 2021.1 compatibility.

I have a branch that works with 2021.1 EAP. I'm not ready to merge it due to the error message @hacker1024 identified. I'm not sure that code is intended for production. I submitted [an issue](https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/IDEA-263745) to see if it is.
Thanks for the work-around for that error @beansoft ! Hopefully the dev channel will have a plugin for the EAP soon. Possibly this weekend, if I can get a quick review on the PR.

The latest dev build's upper version constraint is too low for the latest EAP build.
Here's a patched version to use as a workaround.
`55.0.5-dev.2`: [flutter-intellij.zip](https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/files/6127625/flutter-intellij.zip)

title: Support 2021.1 EAP
